### FAQ-008 | Category: Payments
Canonical Question: How long does it take for my payment to be processed?
Keywords: long, does, take, payment, processed, instantly, time, purchase., once, confirmed, order, activated
Answer:
Your payment is processed instantly at the time of purchase. Once your payment is confirmed, the order is activated immediately, and the seller will arrange dispatch as soon as possible.

If your payment has been made but the order hasn't been collected or shipped, you can cancel it by following these steps:
1.Open the LULUFULO app and log in to your account.
2.Go to “Account” → “My Orders”.
3.Click on “To be shipped”, then find the order you wish to cancel.
4.Tap on “Details”, then select “Return”. Enter any remarks and submit your request.
ii. If your order is already “Out for Delivery”, direct cancellation is not supported at this stage.
You may:
Contact the rider to refuse the parcel upon delivery, or
If collecting in person, do not provide the collection code to complete verification.
Once the delivery attempt fails, you can then follow the steps above to submit a cancellation and refund request. The seller will review your request after confirming the delivery status.
iii. If the order has already been collected or received, direct cancellation is not possible. However, if there are issues such as product defects, wrong items delivered, or missing items, follow these steps instead:
1.Open the LULUFULO app and log in to your account.
2.Go to “Account” → “My Orders”.
3.Locate the order and tap on “Details”.
4.Select “Return”, choose the reason, and provide a description.
5.The merchant will review your after-sales request. If a return is required, send the item back to the address provided by the merchant. Once they confirm receipt of the returned goods, a refund will be processed. If no return is needed, the refund will be issued upon approval.
Merchants will review after-sales requests within 24 hours. Refunds are usually processed within 1-3 working days upon approval, depending on your payment method. If your request is denied, you can view the reasons in “Details” and resubmit your request. Should both parties fail to reach an agreement, please contact our platform's customer service for assistance.

