### FAQ-030 | Category: Discounts&Points
Canonical Question: How to use and redeem points?
Alternate Questions:
- What can I exchange with the points earned from sharing?
Keywords: use, redeem, points, exchange, earned, from, sharing, lulufulo, used, offset, part, order
Answer:
LULUFULO Points can be used to offset part of your order total at checkout, subject to the following rules:
Redemption rate: 1,000 points = USD 1.00 off your payment amount.
Usage limit: Points can cover up to 20% of the final payable amount (after all other discounts, vouchers, or promotions are applied).
Minimum unit: Points must be used in increments of 1,000 (e.g., 1,000, 2,000, 3,000…).
Non-transferable & non-refundable: Points cannot be transferred, exchanged for cash, or shared with other accounts.
Calculation basis: Points are applied after all other discounts — meaning they reduce the discounted order total, not the original price.
Note on earning limits:
You can earn up to 50,000 points per day and 1,000,000 points per month.
Once you reach either limit, no further points will be awarded until the quota resets at 00:00 the next day (daily) or 00:00 on the 1st of the following month (monthly).
To redeem points, simply select them during checkout — the system will automatically apply the maximum eligible amount based on your balance and order value.

